Documentation for Counter App
Overview

This document outlines the structure, styles, and functionality of the Counter App, which allows users to increment and decrement a counter while logging the values to display the history of changes. The application is built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
File Structure

graphql

project-root/
│
├── index.html              # Main HTML file for the Counter App
├── contact.html            # Contact form HTML file
├── css/
│   ├── style.css           # Styles for the Counter App
│   └── general.css         # General styles
└── js/
    └── script.js           # JavaScript functionality

HTML Structure
Main HTML (index.html)

Contains the layout for the Counter App, including the header, main counter display, buttons for interaction, and the footer.
Contact HTML (contact.html)

A simple contact form that captures user information.
CSS Styles
General Styles (style.css)

Styles for the layout, fonts, and color schemes of the app.
Component Styles

Styles for individual components such as buttons, input fields, and the counter display.
JavaScript Functionality (script.js)

Handles the core functionality of the Counter App, including:

    Counter Functionality: Increments and decrements the counter based on user interaction.
    Local Storage: Stores the current count and logged results in the browser's local storage.
    Error Handling: Displays messages if the user attempts to log an empty count.

Usage

    Open the App: Load the index.html file in a web browser.
    Interact with the Counter: Click buttons to increment or decrement the counter. You can also reset the count.
    Log Results: Click "Log Count" to log the current value, which is stored and displayed.
    Clear History: Use the "Clear Counter Board" option to clear logged results.

Conclusion

This Counter App demonstrates the use of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to create an interactive user experience. Future enhancements could include more complex logging features, user authentication, or the ability to save multiple counts.
